\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
a_{0}\\
a_{1}\\
a_{2}\\
a_{3}\\
a_{4}\\
a_{5}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
0\\
1\\
-\nicefrac{1}{2}\\
0
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can write the 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 function and its derivatives explicitly as:
